page.title: 13A nature walk near Bubwith
page.content: We went on a walk around Bubwith countryside our group planned past the river to the woods. We saw bits of interesting things including reeds, thistles, hawthorn, dog roses, clovers,ivy,hemlock, frenchchanesbill,brambles,stickybuds, lords and ladies,sycamore trees, buttercups,daisies, and animals like wasps,bees,cows,birds,sparrows, different finches, a dead mouse and a live mouse. The different fish are pike,perch,gudgin,eel,chub,minnous and sticklebacks.We also know that there are waterhens and water rats even though we did not see any. The wild life around Bubwith is mostly responsible for making Bubwith so pleasent.When walking along the river please try to avoid disturbing the birds and other animals.
